cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

The paper deals with the application of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to semantic labelling of high-resolution remote sensing data. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of pre-trained CNNs and fine-tuning, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of labelling high-resolution aerial imagery involves geometric reasoning and spatial analysis, which are relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
